---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---
<BaseLayout
  title="Accessibility Checker FAQ"
  description="Answers about automated accessibility checks, WCAG mapping, PDF reports, and the limits of a zero-budget hosted scanner."
>
  <section class="section card">
    <h1>FAQ</h1>
    <h2>Does this guarantee ADA compliance?</h2>
    <p class="muted">No. This is an automated check that helps find common issues. Manual review is still necessary.</p>
    <h2>Why is scanning asynchronous?</h2>
    <p class="muted">The scanner uses GitHub Actions as a zero-budget background runner, so jobs are queued instead of running instantly in the browser.</p>
    <h2>What standards are covered?</h2>
    <p class="muted">The MVP reports automated findings tagged to WCAG 2.2 AA where the underlying rules expose those tags.</p>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
